1. An in vitro study was conducted.
2. The study used the fluid filtration method.
3. The study evaluated the effects of medication with calcium hydroxide.
4. The effects were evaluated on the sealing ability of the New Endodontic Cement (NEC) apical barrier.
5. The study looked at the effects in both the short and long terms.

messages.content:
Statement: Using the fluid filtration method, an in vitro study was conducted to evaluate the effects of medication with calcium hydroxide on the sealing ability of the New Endodontic Cement (NEC) apical barrier in the short and long terms.
